  <Method>
    <Step type="STEP" image="">Peel and cut potatoes into 3/4 inch cubes. Cut chicken into 3/4 inch cubes.</Step>
    <Step type="STEP" image="Chicken%20Goulash_20260108_155603.jpg">Heat 1 tbsp of butter in heavy skillet. Add chicken and brown on all sides. Transfer to bowl to hold.</Step>
    <Step type="STEP" image="Chicken%20Goulash_20260108_154537.jpg">Add 1 tbsp butter to skillet. Add potatoes and brown on all sides. Transfer to bowl to hold.</Step>
    <Step type="STEP" image="">Add onions to skillet, cook until softened. Add a little chicken stock to deglaze pan.</Step>
    <Step type="STEP" image="Chicken%20Goulash_20260108_160222.jpg">Transfer onions and juice to large stock pot. Add chicken, potatoes, garlic and remaining stock. </Step>
    <Step type="STEP" image="Chicken%20Goulash_20260108_160406.jpg">Add salt, pepper, msg, poultry seasoning and paprika to pot.</Step>
    <Step type="STEP" image="Chicken%20Goulash_20260108_160456.jpg">Being to a boil, reduce to a simmer and cook for about 45 minutes.</Step>
    <Step type="STEP" image="Chicken%20Goulash_20260108_161051.jpg">Add sliced olives.</Step>
    <Step type="STEP" image="Chicken%20Goulash_20260108_165702.jpg">Simmer and additional 10 minutes, adjust seasoning and serve.</Step>
  </Method>
  <Variations/>
</Recipe>